{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0655f96f0c853d5b51ba9ff6792ec0d7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe LLM verifier is intentionally scoped to no-tools mode to prevent it from discovering new evidence rather than verifying existing claims.\n\nFrom `src/cluster.ts:467-495`, the verifier prompt instructs:\n\n```ts\nreturn [\n  \"You are verifying a factsheet for AgentSessionRouter.\",\n  \"For each fact, decide whether the supplied evidence semantically supports the claim.\",\n  \"Return VERIFIED only when the claim follows from the evidence.\",\n  \"Return UNVERIFIED when support is missing or the claim names APIs/config that are not shown.\",\n  \"Return AMBIGUOUS when the evidence is related but insufficient.\",\n  \"Do not infer. Do not use tools. Return JSON only.\",\n  ...\n].join(\"\\n\");\n```\n\nThe directive **\"Do not use tools\"** is embedded in the prompt itself. Using `agent` mode would allow the verifier to run `Agent`/`Glob`/`Read` and potentially hallucinate evidence that wasn't in the original factsheet — defeating the purpose of verification.\n\nAdditionally, `bare` mode (`--bare --tools \"\"`) was measured to be the cheapest and fastest profile in the experiments referenced in `docs/CLUSTER_CACHE_SPEC.md:19-21`:\n\n> - Broad exploration consult: 264.8s, 56,051 input tokens, `Agent` + `Glob` + `Read`\n> - Fresh `--bare --tools \"\"` with verified factsheet: 36.8s, 1,170 input tokens\n\nThe verifier is also called with `profilePromptOptions(toolProfile)` at `src/cluster.ts:369`, which for `bare` produces `[\"--bare\", \"--tools\", \"\"]` — a purely no-tools invocation that aligns with the prompt constraint."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":103208,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b299724c-1497-410c-96dd-2f782477c674","uuid":"ba967dc5-5e29-48ff-9913-6075a063aedf"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":7938,"duration_api_ms":7910,"num_turns":1,"result":"\n\nThe LLM verifier is intentionally scoped to no-tools mode to prevent it from discovering new evidence rather than verifying existing claims.\n\nFrom `src/cluster.ts:467-495`, the verifier prompt instructs:\n\n```ts\nreturn [\n  \"You are verifying a factsheet for AgentSessionRouter.\",\n  \"For each fact, decide whether the supplied evidence semantically supports the claim.\",\n  \"Return VERIFIED only when the claim follows from the evidence.\",\n  \"Return UNVERIFIED when support is missing or the claim names APIs/config that are not shown.\",\n  \"Return AMBIGUOUS when the evidence is related but insufficient.\",\n  \"Do not infer. Do not use tools. Return JSON only.\",\n  ...\n].join(\"\\n\");\n```\n\nThe directive **\"Do not use tools\"** is embedded in the prompt itself. Using `agent` mode would allow the verifier to run `Agent`/`Glob`/`Read` and potentially hallucinate evidence that wasn't in the original factsheet — defeating the purpose of verification.\n\nAdditionally, `bare` mode (`--bare --tools \"\"`) was measured to be the cheapest and fastest profile in the experiments referenced in `docs/CLUSTER_CACHE_SPEC.md:19-21`:\n\n> - Broad exploration consult: 264.8s, 56,051 input tokens, `Agent` + `Glob` + `Read`\n> - Fresh `--bare --tools \"\"` with verified factsheet: 36.8s, 1,170 input tokens\n\nThe verifier is also called with `profilePromptOptions(toolProfile)` at `src/cluster.ts:369`, which for `bare` produces `[\"--bare\", \"--tools\", \"\"]` — a purely no-tools invocation that aligns with the prompt constraint.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"b299724c-1497-410c-96dd-2f782477c674","total_cost_usd":0.074509,"usage":{"input_tokens":2555,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":103968,"output_tokens":390,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creati